 structure for images and other media assets"}], "architecture_decisions": ["{\"decision\": \"Use static HTML/CSS approach\", \"rationale\": \"Simple, fast-loading, and meets all acceptance criteria without complexity\"}", "{\"decision\": \"Implement mobile-first responsive design\", \"rationale\": \"Ensures accessibility across all devices from the start\"}", "{\"decision\": \"Separate content (HTML), presentation (CSS), and assets\", \"rationale\": \"Clean separation of concerns for maintainability and clarity\"}"]}, "interfaces": [{"name": "HTML Structure", "description": "Semantic HTML5 document with header, main, footer, and content sections"}, {"name": "CSS Styling", "description": "External stylesheet for responsive design, typography, and visual presentation"}, {"name": "Asset Management", "description": "Directory structure for images and other media assets"}], "architecture_decisions": ["{\"decision\": \"Use static HTML/CSS approach\", \"rationale\": \"Simple, fast-loading, and meets all acceptance criteria without complexity\"}", "{\"decision\": \"Implement mobile-first responsive design\", \"rationale\": \"Ensures accessibility across all devices from the start\"}", "{\"decision\": \"Separate content (HTML), presentation (CSS), and assets\", \"rationale\": \"Clean separation of concerns for maintainability and clarity\"}", "{\"decision\": \"Refactor from Tailwind CSS to vanilla CSS\", \"rationale\": \"Align with remediation requirement for simple static HTML/CSS and original shared plan\"}"]}}}
